key_points: The Washington, D.C., area begins cleanup after being impacted by tornadoes and floods from the remnants of Hurricane Ida.
High water and fallen trees hindered the morning commute in several locations.
A tornado in Edgewater, Maryland, caused significant damage, including tossing a pickup truck and downing trees and power lines.
Amtrak canceled all service between Washington and Boston due to the aftermath.
Frederick County Public Schools were closed Thursday following the severe weather.
A flood warning remained in effect in Frederick County, Maryland, with the Monocacy River rising significantly above flood stage.
The National Weather Service plans to investigate two reported tornadoes in Maryland.
The tornado in Anne Arundel County caused extensive damage, including downing electrical wires and damaging homes.
South River High School's football stadium was damaged by the storm.
Anne Arundel Police expressed gratitude to first responders from neighboring areas for their help.
